<item>
            <title>[CONFIGURATION-23] [Configuration] Property throwExceptionOnMissing is not respected for subsets</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CONFIGURATION-23</link>
                <project id="12310467" key="CONFIGURATION">Commons Configuration</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;public void testNoSuchElementExceptionFoSubsets() {&lt;br/&gt;
    BaseConfiguration config = new BaseConfiguration();&lt;br/&gt;
    config.setThrowExceptionOnMissing(true);&lt;br/&gt;
    config.addProperty(&quot;subset.foo&quot;, &quot;bar&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
    try &lt;/p&gt;
{
        config.getString(&quot;subset.foobar&quot;);
        fail(&quot;NoSuchElementException expected&quot;);
    }
&lt;p&gt; catch(NoSuchElementException e) &lt;/p&gt;
{
        // expected
    }&lt;br/&gt;
    try {
        config.subset(&quot;subset&quot;).getString(&quot;foobar&quot;);
        fail(&quot;NoSuchElementException expected&quot;);
    } catch(NoSuchElementException e) {        // expected    }
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This behaviour is currently a showstopper, since I rely on the thrown exception.&lt;br/&gt;
Note: subset() returns a plain Configuration interface, that does not have the&lt;br/&gt;
setThrowExceptionOnMissing setter.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
